    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** - May 15, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 💳 ChatGPT opened the wallet drawer\n\nOpenAI looked at budgeting apps and decided the missing feature was a model quietly reading the card statement. Very normal platform expansion, nothing sensitive here.\n\n- **The preview:** OpenAI launched a U.S. Pro preview that lets ChatGPT connect financial accounts, show spending dashboards and answer questions grounded in a user's money data.\n- **The rails:** account linking runs through Plaid, Intuit support is planned, and OpenAI says more than 12,000 financial institutions are supported at launch.\n- **The guardrails:** ChatGPT cannot see full account numbers or move money, and connected financial data can be disconnected and deleted from OpenAI systems within 30 days.\n\n*The spreadsheet was annoying, so naturally the next step is a financial copilot with memory.*\n\n**Sources:** [OpenAI](https://openai.com/index/personal-finance-chatgpt/)\n\n---\n\n## 📱 Codex got promoted to commute software\n\nThe coding agent now follows you onto the phone, because apparently bugs also deserve push notifications.\n\n- **The rollout:** OpenAI put Codex into the ChatGPT mobile app in preview on iOS and Android, across all plans including Free and Go.\n- **The plumbing:** the phone can review live threads, terminal output, screenshots, diffs, approvals and model choices while the actual files and credentials stay on the laptop, devbox or remote environment.\n- **The enterprise bit:** Remote SSH and Hooks are now available on all plans; programmatic access tokens are for Business and Enterprise.\n\n*Long-running agents are becoming a work surface. The desk is no longer a boundary condition.*\n\n**Sources:** [OpenAI](https://openai.com/index/work-with-codex-from-anywhere/)\n\n---\n\n## 🧾 Anthropic found the small-business spreadsheet pile\n\nClaude is going after the businesses that still treat operations as a heroic blend of inboxes, invoices and late-night tabs. Glamour, but with bookkeeping.\n\n- **The product:** Anthropic launched Claude for Small Business, connecting Claude to QuickBooks, PayPal, HubSpot, Canva, Docusign, Google Workspace and Microsoft 365.\n- **The workflows:** Anthropic says Claude can help plan payroll, close the month, run sales campaigns, chase invoices and handle other recurring operations.\n- **The market signal:** TechCrunch reported Ramp data showing 34.4% of participating businesses now pay for Anthropic services versus 32.3% for OpenAI, Anthropic's first lead in that index.\n\n*The AI adoption curve has reached the invoice reminder. Civilization trembles.*\n\n**Sources:** [Anthropic](https://www.anthropic.com/news/claude-for-small-business?hsLang=en) | [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/13/anthropic-now-has-more-business-customers-than-openai-according-to-ramp-data/)\n\n---\n\n## 🧇 Cerebras made wafer-scale money look small\n\nThe AI chip market wanted a public benchmark for inference mania. Cerebras obligingly arrived with a valuation chart wearing a jetpack.\n\n- **The IPO:** Reuters says Cerebras priced 30 million shares at $185, raising $5.55 billion and implying a $56.43 billion fully diluted valuation.\n- **The demand:** Reuters reported orders exceeded available shares by more than 20 times after Cerebras raised both its price range and share count.\n- **The customer list:** TechCrunch notes Cerebras counts OpenAI, G42, MBZUAI and AWS among customers for inference compute.\n\n*When token demand becomes infrastructure demand, even the prospectus starts sweating.*\n\n**Sources:** [Reuters via Investing.com](https://www.investing.com/news/stock-market-news/cerebras-prices-ipo-at-185-per-share-to-raise-555-billion-sources-say-4686852) | [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/14/cerebras-raises-5-5b-kicking-off-2026s-ipo-season-with-a-bang/)\n\n---\n\n## ⚖️ Musk and OpenAI reached the jury-shaped cliff\n\nThe industry's founding-family argument has arrived at closing statements, because apparently the future of AI also needed courtroom lore.\n\n- **The case:** AP says lawyers for Elon Musk and OpenAI delivered final arguments Thursday in the Oakland trial over whether OpenAI betrayed its founding nonprofit mission.\n- **The claim:** Musk's 2024 lawsuit accuses Sam Altman and OpenAI leadership of shifting the organization toward profit behind his back.\n- **The stakes:** the outcome could influence how much contractual weight early AI-safety promises carry once labs become infrastructure companies with giant balance sheets.\n\n*The mission statement has entered evidence. Silicon Valley may need a chair.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/musk-sam-altman-openai-trial-closing-arguments-3bda5ebbec28c23ac9e481a4edcad725)"
  }
]
